rComments: Prof. Pesando is one of the gems of UofTs Economics Department. He has the best lectures and you wont need to read textbooks if you attend them. However, he has hard tests especially if you dont understand the foundational concepts. It is also very important to practice a lot before going to his midterms. Overall, I like his teaching!

He's funny and clearly explains the concepts. The problem is that memorizing his notes isn't what's going to get you a good grade. He's a tough grader and his tests are harder than other profs'. His tests are vague and if your arguments aren't exactly the ones on his answer sheet, you get half the marks. His lectures don't prepare you for tests.
teacherRatingTags: ['Test heavy', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader']

rComments: His lectures are beautiful. No need for textbook use whatsoever. I'd suggest going to lectures since he explains it so well and his voice is so soothing, but his notes are super clear anyways.
He provides really good foundation of your understanding of economics
Awesome prof, super clear and straightforward. If you are a first year student, MAKE SURE TO CHOOSE HIM AS YOUR PROF.
I didn't even open the textbook a single time, his notes are so good and concise and his personality is infectious
Good prof. before this class every one said his class is quite easier than another. however, it is true, but still hard in understanding lecture and doing well on the test.
Pretty good for eco101. Its a tough course in general so youre gonna have to put in the work. Do lots of previous practice tests and youll be golden.
I would want to listen to his lectures again in year two.
I really enjoy professor Pesando's lecture. He is an amazing professor I've ever seen before. He is responsible for students and respectable. He explained every economic concepts very detail.
Must have prior Economics experience
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Participation matters', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Best Eco class! If you are RC student, don't miss this professor!

He is a very good professor. His lectures are clear and concise, and he can be amusing to boot. The tests are not overly difficult, although it is crucial to understand all of the concepts thoroughly.
pretty good

You don't realize that he is one of the best profs until you don't have him anymore. Definitely the hardest course I took in my first semester, but if you do the past tests and understand them you will be fine. Worked my ass off for a B-. If you're not a math person, he would be the best choice as he doesn't use numbers very often,mostly theory.
Great guy and awesome prof!

A really amazing professor, no doubt I would take him again! His lectures are explained very clearly and detailed. Although generally, ECO101 is difficult, you have to master the concepts to be able to score. Tests are challenging if you don't know the concepts but very fair otherwise. He is easily one of the best professors there for ECO101 :)

Despite what everyone says, he is actually a very good professor! The best way to succeed in this class is by doing past tests and going to tutorials, which become very helpful when it comes to studying for tests. Even if you bomb the first test (like me) theres still a chance, you just have to work for it and put in all your effort!
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Graded by few things', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: ECO101. HE IS amazing! his lecture notes are very good. I would highly recommend studying from past tests and go to the ecoman because he has loads of past tests. VERY important to religiously study the examples that are not in the lecture notes, he always puts these questions on tests and exams! Tests are not hard.

The course in general is pretty difficult but Professor Pesando's lectures are extremely helpful in breaking down some counter intuitive concepts. You need to put in some work outside of class to do well though.
Attend his lectures regularly. he does not share all the lecture slides , so get ready to type / write notes . Look for what he says in between the lines , those are the key words.

ECO100 is my favorite class and Professor Pesando is my favorite professor. He is truly the best and he made economis very interesting to learn. Strongly recommend his class (usually L0101) to everyone!
LOVE him but his tests are killer. Maybe 3 weeks of studying will be enough to get you a decent grade
He is simply an amazing professor
The grading is really hard; however, his lectures, in particular, and this course, in general, are really interesting.

Prof. Pessando takes the time to ensure clarity in his lectures, gives many examples. There is a lot of information to grasp in ECO100. Tests are seldom, but hard. Assignments are not graded, but if you don't do them, you won't understand the material.
the best prof ever seen. his lectures are just so clear and helpful.

Love this prof, he's so clear and everyone is enticed when he speaks. Gives great examples during class. Tests and finals are very hard. Practice past exams!! Many retakes this course because its really hard the first time

Best prof I've had in first year. Very inspirational. Tests are a tad bit hard but if you do the past exams you're good to go. He ensures that you have a thorough understanding of economics as a subject. Changed my view over economics.
He is the best professor, it was his last year and the whole class was emotional when it was our last class, he is truly the best.
super nice! love this professor! make eco100 interesting!
Excellent professor
He is an amazing prof. You respect him more and more every day and is amazing at what he does. He is very nice to his students and very helpful too. Definitely choose him!!!
great class! choose pesando as your prof! he's so helpful and nice, so talk to him when you have any trouble doing better in eco!!!

rComments: Pesando must be one of the most experienced professor in the whole UofT. His lectures are amazing. He knows what students might be confused and how to answer those confusions. Make notes of lectures and study the notes, better than textbook. Finish all the assignments and go to all the tutorials and you will get a fairly good mark.
teacherRatingTags: ['Amazing lectures', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader']

rComments: Awesome prof

He is really a good teacher and he knows a lot. He knows how to teach us in an easy and clear way. But he teaches really really fast! He doesn't give us any slides so we have to take notes  and listen to him at the same time. Sometimes it's hard to get his speed. It's better to review every time after class.
He's good

I had prof Pesando for micro and prof Indart for macro and the difference between them is crazy. Prof Pesando was amazing! You actually paid attention in his lectures and he made eco interesting. While his are hard, do the past tests and you'll be fine. Attending his lectures is a must! I really enjoyed eco with him!
Lectures are interesting, but it's hard to listen while writing so many notes in class. Focus on learning and understanding the graphs and you should do fine.
Very good professor. Still miss the professor and his class after 3 years of graduation. Very helpful on building a economic foundation of life.
Excellent professor, textbook seemed unhelpful compared to his explainations. The only class I kept full attendance.
One of UT's best profs. Lectures notes are extremely helpful, NEVER MISS CLASS!

No need to worry about the other class having a higher average from the mid terms. All the hard work will be paid off on the final exam which is 50% of the whole course. Make sure you get all his inclass notes since he does not upload them.

Pesando is a great prof. His notes are organized and his lectures are clear and insightful. His tests aren't as hard as people make it out to be, just do enough past tests and you'll get the hang of it.

Pesando was a decent lecturer. He teaches quite well. Save your money and don't buy the textbooks, his notes help much much more. You need to attend every class since he does not post his notes online. His tests are quite difficult as well, so prepare yourself. Overall, he was a decent teacher.

Professor Pesando's lectures were clear and to the point. Very helpful and nice guy. However, I did find his tests difficult - but this could be because I was not used to his teaching style. Overall, I find him to be a very nice and helpful guy. He definitely opened up my views of Economics.

He is an amazing professor. He makes economics interesting, and certainly, his tests are probably the most difficult I have written yet, but it's all worth it because the way he makes you think. Definitely try to get into his section. He is also very helpful if you go to him during his office hours or after class.
Best Professor so far

He's an amazing prof! I've never learned econ in hs and gotta admit his tests can be really challenging. Lectures are interesting. Attend to all lectures & tutorials, practice practice practice and think of the possible questions that might be on the tests, then you'll do great.

Very very organized in his delivering. No time to waste in his lecture. Answers all doubts if you ask him after lecture. Tests focused more on intuition and whether you really understand the topics and not so much mathematical. Enjoyed his class!
He's a great prof!!!!!
very organized lecture and clear explanation with real world application. Best wish with all respect from 2011-2012 eco100 student
Probably the best ECO100 prof. This course is the only class I attend since his stories (on economic application) is interesting. Also, his test is not hard as people say
Amazing professor.  Very intuitive and inspiring lectures!

He's a great prof with fascinating stories. Although challenging, his class will teach you real life applications of economics. In addition, his TAs are always great and will help a lot in this class! Take him if you truly want to learn.

Teaches the subject matter very well. Doesn't use as much math to justify his claims, but is able to convey his point for the most part. Tests are designed to be challenging without being impossible; not the regurgitation kind of tests, which is nice.

Great prof !
best prof in eco100!!

Prof. Pesando delivers organized and comprehensive lectures. An inspirational professor - he exudes brilliance and charisma at every lecture. You're sure to enjoy his class!

Amazing lecturer, probably the best for ECO100.  Simplifies concepts making them easier to understand.  HARD tests, expects students to use higher level thinking especially because he only teaches commerce students (& expects them to be smarter than the norm). Study hard to understand course material and you'll do well. The final is easier though.

Extremely clear and organized with lecture material. Gives practical real-life examples of abstract economic concepts. Arguably the best prof for eco100 in terms of understanding. Tests have twists, so must pay close attention to details. Amazing experience overall.
very hard tests, good prof but his test r just gay lol
